abstract_ssm: This collection consists of correspondence, flyers, and administrative files related to socialist activist Joanne Landy's work as an editor for New Politics magazine and as an organizer for the Campaign for Peace and Democracy. The materials cover the editorial and administrative processes involved in publishing New Politics during the 1980s through the early 2000s and the social and intellectual context of the advocacy Landy organized with the Campaign for Peace and Democracy. The files are both paper and electronic, though the majority of the records are paper. The files on the Campaign for Peace and Democracy include audio and video recordings of talks by Landy pertaining to the organization's activism.
